/* ============================================================================
   Jewish History Explorer — the dual-track timeline data layer
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   THREE globals:
     window.TAXO       — categories, verdicts, tracks + the time axis (TIME_SLICES)
     window.EVENTS     — the dual-track events (the heart of the app)
     window.MIGRATIONS — the great movements, as globe arcs (with *why*)

   STANCE — evidence-forward & even-handed. Each event leads with `rec` (what the
   archaeological / documentary record shows) and adds `trad` (what the tradition
   recounts). `verdict` names the scholarly consensus on how the tradition fares
   against the evidence — it never "debunks", and treats tradition as a parallel
   layer of memory. Pre-modern figures/locations are illustrative; the map uses
   modern borders at every era as a visualization device.

   EVENT shape:
     { id, year, end?, title, place, iso, lat, lng,
       cat,                     // TAXO.categories key — kind of event (pin colour)
       track,                   // 'record' | 'tradition' | 'both'
       verdict,                 // TAXO.verdicts key (for 'both'/'tradition'); 'documented' for record-only
       rec, trad,               // the two sides (rec leads; trad may be '')
       why?, src:[] }           // optional cause; short source tags
     year/end are signed years — negative = BCE.

   MIGRATION shape:
     { id, start, end, from:{lat,lng,place}, to:{lat,lng,place},
       label, why, kind:'forced'|'voluntary'|'return', track, magnitude }
   ========================================================================== */
'use strict';

